I"P<h3 id="one-of-my-new-years-resolutions">One of my new year’s resolutions</h3>

<p><strong>I never liked math…</strong> Until this year, until I got into programming seriously. Although I now enjoy math and science that doesn’t change the fact that I’m not very good at it. I’m getting better but I’m still not exceptional.</p>

<p>Thanks to my only god: <strong>the internet</strong> I discovered that algorithms and data structures are considered the fundamentals of computer science. That means that’s where I’m headed now ! Apparently two basic types of algorithms are searching and sorting algorithms. So here it goes.</p>

