<p>and</p>

<p><img src="/post-assets/bubble_sort.png" alt="Bubble sort" /></p>

<p>I just remembered that I also implemented the Sieve of Eratosthenes algorithm.</p>

<p><img src="/post-assets/primes.png" alt="Sieve of Eratosthenes" /></p>

<p>When I checked my Sieve of Eratosthenes program for correctness I realized that I’d made a terrible mistake: <strong>my program ran for n times instead of square root of n times</strong>. I was absolutely shook because I remember that my math teacher mentioned such a thing. I think it’s at that moment that I really regretted not listening more in math class.</p>

<p>This <a href="&quot;https://github.com/karan/Projects#classic-algorithms&quot;">repo</a> really helped me find projects to get started with algorithms. I’m not finished with the projects but I’m really eager to start using data structures. I’ll keep y’all up to date!</p>
